function buildArray(target, n) {
    const result = [];
    let current = 1;
    for (const num of target) {
        while (current < num) {
            result.push("Push");
            result.push("Pop");
            current++;
        }
        result.push("Push");
        current++;
    }
    return result;
}
```

    The algorithm iterates through the `target` array. For each number, it checks if the `current` value (starting from 1) is smaller. If it is, the algorithm adds the "Push" and "Pop" operations to the result list, because these numbers in `list` are not part of the `target` array. The `current` value is then incremented. Once the `current` value reaches the `num` in the target array, the algorithm adds a "Push" operation to the result list and increments the `current` value again. This process continues until the entire target array has been built using the operations listed in the result list.

